HEADWORD: Alborak
<hw>Al"bo*rak</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>al-bur⟦amac⟧q</ets>, fr. <ets>baraqa</ets> to flash, shine.]</ety>
<def>The imaginary milk-white animal on which Mohammed was said to have
been carried up to heaven; a white mule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alb Sunday</ent>⟦br⟧
